HEADWORD: Frame of reference
<hw>Frame of reference</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>an arbitrary set of spatial coordinates used to describe the
position or motion of objects. The coordinates may be fixed or moving;
<as>as, a rotating <ex>frame of reference</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a set of assumptions or conditions that are used to
discuss or understand something; <as>as, a religious <ex>frame of
reference</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Framer</ent>⟦br⟧
